<TITLE> ACC sues ambassador to UAE </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission Wednesday sued the Bangladesh ambassador to the United Arab Emirates, Nazimullah Chowdhury, on charges of abusing power and misusing state funds. The envoy cost the state coffers Tk 21 lakh in losses, the ACC alleged quoting an initial investigation. The envoy is accused of shifting the ambassador's home to a more expensive location in Abu Dhabi, buying household materials and appointing gardeners by misappropriating money. Deputy director of the ACC Abdullah Al Zahid who filed the case made a trip to the UAE in February to probe corruption allegations against the envoy and other embassy officials. The graft case is the first against any ambassador of the country as part of the government's anticorruption crackdown. bd
